      • addToPerimeter

        public void addToPerimeter(java.util.ArrayList<MapPoint> island,
                           GeographicArea.BoundaryType type)
        This method converts an ordered set of MapPoints to a closed java.awt.geom.Path2D. The path is then added to adds that path to a java.awt.geom.Area.

        java.awt.geom.Path2D expects points to be 2D cartesian coordinates; however this method adds untransformed latitude and longitude points. While this creates a distorted space that cannot correctly measure distances, the methods we need contains() and perimeter calculation, will work with the untransformed latitude and longitude coordinates.

        island -
